Refactored the LLM config/auth path in three places.

In [llm_config.h](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/llm/base/llm_config.h#L14) and [llm_config.cpp](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/llm/base/llm_config.cpp#L247), `LLMConfig` no longer loads defaults or hunts `.env` in its constructor. The parser now isolates the `"providers"` object first and only extracts provider objects from there, so `"claude_code_sdk"` no longer collides with the `activeProvider` string. I also added explicit `allowedTools` storage to `ProviderConfig`, updated the built-in Claude SDK defaults to include `model: "claude-sonnet-4-6"` in [llm_config.cpp](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/llm/base/llm_config.cpp#L440), removed the noisy per-parse debug log, and relaxed validation so config loading is structural rather than dependent on auth already being present.

In [wibwob_engine.cpp](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/wibwob_engine.cpp#L227), config load now happens once: try the file, otherwise load built-in defaults once, with clear logging for the chosen path and a single final resolved-config log line. In [claude_code_sdk_provider.h](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/llm/providers/claude_code_sdk_provider.h#L47) and [claude_code_sdk_provider.cpp](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/llm/providers/claude_code_sdk_provider.cpp#L697), I added a typed `configure(const ProviderConfig&)` path and [wibwob_engine.cpp](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/wibwob_engine.cpp#L299) now uses it for the Claude SDK provider instead of serializing config to JSON and re-parsing it. The existing string-based configure path is still there for compatibility and the useful `[SDK] Configured model: ...` log remains.

`app/llm/config/llm_config.json` already had the requested Claude SDK defaults in the working tree, so I did not change it in this pass.

Verification: `cd build && make -j1 wwdos` passed. `ctest --output-on-failure` did not fully pass because `command_registry_test` and `scramble_engine_test` executables are missing from this build tree; the two Micropolis tests passed.
